<title>GERMANY: Bavaria May CPI up 0.5 pct mth/mth, 1.1 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Bavaria May CPI up 0.5 pct mth/mth, 1.1 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>MUNICH, Germany 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>The German state of Bavaria said consumer prices in May rose 0.5 percent month-on-month and rose 1.5 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>The Munich-based state statistics office reported a 3.1 percent rise in May for personal goods and services and a 0.4 percent rise in rent and energy costs.</p>
<p>In Apil, the state reported a 0.2 percent month-on-month drop in consumer prices and a 1.1 percent year-on-year rise.</p>
<p>Bavaria is the first of the four west German states to report data for May that will be used to compute provisional west German inflation data for the month.  </p>
<p>The statistics office gave the following breakdown of its May cost of living data :</p>
<p>						 Percentage change</p>
<p> Index/component			   mth/mth   yr/yr    Index</p>
<p> Overall price index		     +0.5	+1.5     115.7</p>
<p> Rents					 +0.3	+2.9     129.2</p>
<p> Personal goods, services and other  +3.1	+2.2     123.9</p>
<p> Transport and communications	  +0.0	-0.6     115.4</p>
<p> Furniture and other household goods -0.1	+0.4     110.0</p>
<p> Foodstuffs, drinks, tobacco	   +0.5	+1.3     110.3</p>
<p> Clothing, shoes			   +0.0	+0.8     107.4</p>
<p> Health and personal care items	-0.1	+1.1     114.9</p>
<p> Education, entertainment, leisure   +0.2	+2.0     111.7</p>
